item.title: Kesha - Praying (Hexx Remake)
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
I like it. I kind of feel like you’re holding back with your voice? I’m no singer, I’ve done my fair share of songs with vocals though and I kind of felt like maybe you were singing and didn’t want to be loud? Been there. I like your take on the Mariah Carey-esque super high pitched part.

The pitch glide square wave is a little wonky. It’s not bad it just comes out of nowhere and maybe it’s a little loud?

I really enjoyed this though I like the tonality of your voice. I think the vocal mixing could use a little massaging (the second half of the songs vocals sounded louder) but it’s not something unsalvageable.

Keeping an ear out for your other vocal stuff I really did like this, just wanted to offer some feedback!
